> Pork makes us think of apples, which make us think of fall and all things cozy, which is why we're practically drooling over this comforting sweet-and-savory meal. As a bonus, cauliflower is snuck into the mashed potatoes for a boost of nutrition and extra silky texture.

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Chop @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into 1-inch cubes. Place in a large #pot{} of salted water along with @cauliflower florets{10%ounce}. Bring to a boil. Cook until fork-tender, ~{12-15%minutes}. Drain and return to pot.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a large pan over high heat. Season @pork tenderloin{12%ounce} on all sides with @salt{} and @pepper{}, and @dried thyme{1%teaspoon}. Add to pan, and sear until golden brown all around, ~{1-2%minutes} per side.

== Roasting ==

Trim @sugar snap peas{6%ounce}. When pork has browned, transfer to one half of a #baking sheet{}. Add snap peas to other half, and toss with a drizzle of oil and pinch of salt and pepper. Roast until pork is cooked to desired doneness (we like ours slightly pink) and snap peas are bright and tender, ~{10-12%minutes}.

== Apple Pan Sauce ==

While pork cooks, core and thinly slice @Granny Smith apple{1}. Heat @butter{1%tablespoon} and a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium heat. Add apple slices. Toss until softened and slightly golden, ~{3-5%minutes}. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Add @chicken stock concentrate{1} and @water{1/2%cup}. Simmer on low until thickened, ~{3-5%minutes}.

== Potato Cauliflower Mash ==

Add @butter{1%tablespoon} to cauliflower and potatoes. Mash with a #fork{} or #potato masher{} until smooth. Season generously with salt and pepper. Reheat over low if necessary.

== Assembly ==

Thinly slice the roasted pork tenderloin. Serve on a bed of potato cauliflower mash with snap peas on the side. Drizzle with apple pan sauce and enjoy!